description: Universal checklist for confirming a feature or task is truly complete.
alwaysApply: true
---

# DEFINITION OF DONE

Before declaring any feature, fix, or task complete, confirm all of the following:

## Code Quality
- [ ] Lint passes with no new errors introduced
- [ ] No obvious crash paths added (null access, unhandled promise rejections, missing error states)
- [ ] No unrelated files changed

## Behavior
- [ ] Feature works as described in the original request
- [ ] Works offline or fails gracefully with a user-friendly message
- [ ] No regression in adjacent screens or features

## Communication
- [ ] Plain-English summary of what changed and why is ready to log
- [ ] Any new decisions are noted in DECISION_LOG.md

## Testing
- [ ] If code was touched: device test required (defer to testing-protocol rule for exact steps)
- [ ] If content-only: no device test needed

## Documentation
- [ ] PATCH_NOTES.md entry written or queued
- [ ] PROJECT_CONTEXT.md updated if phase status, flags, or decisions changed

## Reuse Notes
- Keep this rule always-on across projects.
- Adjust checklist items to match project-specific quality gates as needed.
